Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.86,floatwindow1,,0000,0000,0000,,前情提要...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.60,0:00:08.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的旅程始于缅甸旧都仰光\NOur adventure began in the old Burmese capital Rangoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.51,0:00:11.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们仨买了三台古老的卡车\Nwhere, having bought three ancient lorries...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.46,0:00:13.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈蒙德 这个是教堂长椅吧\NHammond, this seat is a church pew.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.18,0:00:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们被告知需要在桂河上修建一座桥\Nwe were told we had to build a bridge over the River Kwai that was
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.60,0:00:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来让我们的卡车通过\Nstrong enough to support them.'
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.92,0:00:22.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要造一座多大的桥来支撑我们的卡车\NHow big a bridge are we going to have to build to support my truck?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.38,0:00:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你的车多重 -大概1000吨\NHow much does yours weigh? About 1,000 tonnes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.85,0:00:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了到达那条在泰国的河流 我们需要完成一次1900多公里的旅程\NGetting to the river in Thailand meant a 1,200 mile journey
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.08,0:00:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开车穿越缅甸是一件危险的事情\Nacross Burma on roads that were dangerous...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.85,0:00:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,山峦起伏的\N..mountainous...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.67,0:00:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有的时候甚至完全没有路\N..and often not roads at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.85,0:00:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,空转的厉害 开始侧滑了\NLots of the wheel spin. Sliding badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.70,0:00:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由于制片人总要我们住进缅甸当地的大车店\NSince the producers insisted we stay in Burmese truck stops...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.00,0:00:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 还没那么糟啊\NOh, it's not so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.57,0:00:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们把自己的卡车改造成了房车\N..we turned our lorries into houses.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.44,0:01:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是所有升级都起到了升级的效果\NNot all of my improvements have turned out to be improvements.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.00,0:01:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在一个鸟不拉屎的地方 我们没油了\NWay out in the middle of nowhere, we ran out of fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.00,0:01:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在寻找柴油的路上\Nand whilst looking for diesel...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.46,0:01:14.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈蒙德被一匹种马甩了下来 伤到了胳膊\NHammond was thrown by a stallion and injured his arm.'
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.46,0:01:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更糟糕的是 詹姆斯的鼾声逼我们采取强硬措施\NWorse still, James's snoring forced us to take drastic action.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.78,0:01:23.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,克拉克森\NClarkson!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.57,0:01:26.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管我们去到哪里\NAnd everywhere we went,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.15,0:01:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈蒙德那垂直的排气管都会引发混乱\NHammond's vertical exhausts were causing chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.00,0:01:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,另外一根也掉了\NI've lost my other stack.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.00,0:01:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不是海军陆战队 我们会丢下队友 你懂的\NAs you know, we're not the US Marines, we leave a man behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.68,0:02:08.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不好意思\NSorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.23,0:02:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没啥事 不用围观\NIt's OK. Nothing to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.00,0:02:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在哈蒙德那台随时会解体的卡车前方\NFar ahead of Hammond's disintegrating lorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.32,0:02:27.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,詹姆斯和我即将进入缅甸一个神秘的地方\NJames and I were about to enter a secretive region of Burma
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.04,0:02:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,掸邦\Nknown as the Shan state.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.30,0:02:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,内战已经在这里持续了60年\NA civil war has raged here for 60 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.00,0:02:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有一个摄制组之前被允许进入这里\NNo television crew has ever been allowed in.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.54,0:02:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们会是第一个\NWe would be the first.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.56,0:02:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那里保持神秘是有原因的\NThere is a very good reason why it's so secretive in there. You see
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.00,0:02:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,通常旅行社会告诉你\Nthe travel companies would have you believe
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.00,0:02:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,金三角地区是一个有特色的旅游景点\Nthat the Golden Triangle is, well, it's a tourist attraction,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.00,0:02:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那里是泰国 缅甸和老挝接壤的地方\Nat the point where Thailand, Burma and Laos all meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.09,0:02:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是金三角和这个...\NBut the golden triangle with the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.15,0:03:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我应该怎么说呢\Nhow can I put this
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.12,0:03:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里的特色农产品\Nthe special agriculture - that is in the Shan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.86,0:03:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,显然 有人称之为"马"\NApparently, some of the special agriculture is known as horse,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.00,0:03:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里种的"马"越来越多 我睁大眼找吧\Nthey're obviously growing horses somehow. I shall look for those.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.00,0:03:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成片的"马"田\NFields of horses growing in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.70,0:03:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们到了 热情欢迎您的到来 就是这里\NHere we go. Warm and cordial welcome, this is it. This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.76,0:03:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们正在进入掸邦\NWe are entering the Shan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.76,0:03:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事实上我们代表着西方世界\NWe genuinely are representing the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.00,0:03:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还好我系了领带\NGood job I'm wearing a tie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.04,0:03:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不幸的是 随着路面越来越陡\NUnfortunately, as the roads started to climb,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.81,0:03:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,詹姆斯和我就忘了怎么假正经\NJames and I rather forgot the significance of where we were.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.48,0:03:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不 -加油啊老卡车\NNo! Come on, lorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.79,0:04:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欢迎收看掸邦卡车爬山赛\NWelcome, then, to the inaugural Shan state lorry hill climb.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.89,0:04:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这里一次糟糕的换档\NA sport where a single botched gear change
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.69,0:04:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就可以带来巨大的损失\Ncan make all the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.47,0:04:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尝试挤进内线\NAttempt to squeeze in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.00,0:04:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他过来了\NHe's coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.63,0:04:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要啊 我被一台皮卡挡住了\NNo, no, no! I'm trapped by the pick-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.00,0:04:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吃灰吧\NEat my dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.75,0:04:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,守住内线\NGot the inside line.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.93,0:04:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这绝对是世界上最好的赛事\NThis is the best race in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.00,0:04:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我挡住了他 我挡住了他\NI've blocked him, I blocked him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.00,0:04:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在我们通过城镇的时候可以暂时停战么\NShall we call a temporary truce while we go through the town, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.35,0:04:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们回去之后 如果军情六处来找我们谈话\NWhen we get back, if we're interviewed by MI6
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.15,0:04:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会问 掸邦到底是什么样子的\Nand they say, "What was it like in the Shan?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.36,0:04:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们就说 不知道啊 我们在进行卡车竞速\NWe'll have to go, "I don't know, we were racing lorries."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.84,0:05:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,实在不好意思 作为第一批进入这里的西方人\NI am embarrassed to be the first Westerner in here
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.52,0:05:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我居然开了一台竞速卡车 车头还绑着粉色泰迪熊\Nand I'm driving a sports lorry with a pink teddy bear on the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.00,0:05:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了装装样子 我把的的小熊拿回到了驾驶室\NTo make us look more dignified, I put Rudyard in the cab,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.23,0:05:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们继续向未知的地方进发\Nand then we set off into the unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.76,0:05:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,俄滴神呀\NGod above.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.17,0:05:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想我无意中走上了的捷径\NI think I've accidentally taken a short cut
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.58,0:05:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,通向了"权力与游戏"的片场\Ninto the set of Game Of Thrones.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.58,0:05:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个区域要比英格兰和威尔士加在一起都大\NHere, in a region that is bigger than England and Wales put together,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.70,0:05:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是只有一条150年前由英国人修建的公路\Nthere is just one road, built 150 years ago, by the British.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.96,0:05:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里没有电 没有手机信号 没有电视\NBut there is no electricity, no mobile phone signal, no TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.68,0:05:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有酒店 没有医院\Nno hotels, no hospitals.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.38,0:05:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天上也没有飞机\NAnd in the skies, no planes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.78,0:06:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里实在是太大了\NThat is gigantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.66,0:06:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被这一切折服了 詹姆斯和我把车子停了下来\NBowled over by it all, James and I pulled over,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.00,0:06:11.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随后哈蒙德赶了上来\Nand after Hammond caught up...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.13,0:06:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 上世纪20年代的老爷车来了\NOh, yes, the 1920s is arriving.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.00,0:06:18.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们试着搞明白为什么我们是第一批\N..we tried to work out why us three had been the first ones
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.72,0:06:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被允许进入这里的\Nallowed in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.00,0:06:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想想吧\NThink about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.76,0:06:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你是金三胖 你想让你的人民看看\NIf you were North Korea, and you wanted to portray to your people
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.00,0:06:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,西方世界有多么邋遢和没用\Nhow lumpen and useless the West was,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.69,0:06:32.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你一定会邀请我们三个的 不是么\Nyou'd invite us three, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.10,0:06:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们四处逛时 朝鲜人民会想\NBecause we'd wander about and the North Koreans would go,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.50,0:06:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么要变成西方那样 看看这几个 他们太糟糕了\N"Why would we want to be Western? Look at them. They're dreadful."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.57,0:06:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你肩膀上有小鸟排泄物 -是的\NYou've got bird poo on your shoulder. I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.48,0:06:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以政府的基本意思就是想告诉自己的人民\NSo what the government is essentially saying to these
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.18,0:06:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么要活的像这几个洋鬼子那样\Npeople is, why would you want to live like they do in the West?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.85,0:06:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-看看这几个货 -其实我们另外在做的一件事\NLook at them. There's another thing that we're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.00,0:06:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实是很偶然的\NThis is just an incidental service.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.00,0:06:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里不会总能见到西方人\NThey haven't seen many Westerners here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.00,0:06:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至少我们的出现 不会让他们在最后想\NWe are at least showing... They're not going to end up saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.12,0:06:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实洋人长得都一样\N"They all look the same to me," are they? With us three.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.26,0:07:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你这是严重的种族主义\NThat's just blatantly racist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.41,0:07:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他意思是所有缅甸人在他眼中都一样\NWhat he's saying is all Burmese people look the same to him
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.73,0:07:07.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-才没有 -显然你是这样的\NNo... Clearly. Yes, you are. You are.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.71,0:07:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在假设他们认为我们长得都一样\NYou're assuming that they think we all look the same
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.00,0:07:11.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们认为他们长得都一样\Nbecause we think they all look the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.67,0:07:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在偷换概念 我没有\NNow you're making a leap, I didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.00,0:07:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在添油加醋 我没说过\NYou're completing something that I didn't put in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.11,0:07:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 我俩承认 但就爱逗你玩\NYes, we are, but it's quite good fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.42,0:07:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了继续欣赏掸邦美景 我们重新上路\NKeen to see more of the Shan, we moved on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.00,0:07:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看看这个三蹦子司机\NChaps, check out the driver of this tuk-tuk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.45,0:07:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他干嘛了\NWhat's he done?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.39,0:07:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道具体做了些什么 但是他做了很多\NI don't know what it was, but he's done a lot of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.67,0:07:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他毫无表情啊\NHe's off his face. Oh, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.28,0:07:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天啊 我明白你的意思了\NOh, Lord, I see what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.00,0:08:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,詹姆斯 你看到哪里有种"马"了么\NJames, do you see any fields where they are growing horses?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.00,0:08:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有 我还没看见一个"马"田\NNo, I haven't seen a single horse plantation yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.00,0:08:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我们却看见了\NWhat we did see, however, was evidence of what is officially
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.40,0:08:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,世界上最漫长内战的证据\Nthe world's longest running civil war.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.44,0:08:20.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是不小的一支部队啊\NThis is a big army presence, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.61,0:08:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而詹姆斯却只顾别的小事\NJames, however, seemed to have less important things on his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.00,0:08:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,该试试我的自制水冷刹车系统了\NTime to try out my water brake cooling system.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.92,0:08:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,准备好了 这里有个小开关\NI'm ready. A little switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.60,0:08:44.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想它起作用了\NI think it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.38,0:08:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但好戏没有维持多久\NThe elation however was short lived
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.59,0:08:58.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我去\NCock.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.54,0:09:01.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的方向盘锁死了\NChaps my steering has just locked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.00,0:09:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,詹姆斯 我觉得挡住军车不是一个好主意啊\NI'm not sure that's a good idea, James, is it? Blocking the Army?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.00,0:09:10.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,问题很严重\NThe problem was a big one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.85,0:09:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前轴断了\NThe front axle had broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.07,0:09:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我唯一想到的\NThere's only one thing I can think to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.04,0:09:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,适合在这时候播放的歌曲\Nto play at a time like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.13,0:09:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪抱歉是最难说出的一句话♪(艾尔·顿约翰的歌)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.75,0:09:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,走吧走吧 再见\NWell, off you go. Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.25,0:09:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这实在太惨了 不是么 -再见\NThat's a bad one, isn't it? See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.00,0:09:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪真惨 太惨 简直惨绝人寰♪
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.51,0:09:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈蒙德和我继续深入掸邦\NAs Hammond and I travelled deeper into the Shan,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.31,0:09:57.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,路况变得愈发糟糕\Nthe road became worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.00,0:10:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原因也愈发清楚\N'And the reason why soon became clear.'
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.00,0:10:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那边真的有一个小孩子正在修路\NThat was an actual baby there, building the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.80,0:10:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这可不是什么好政策 因为路面实在太糟糕了\NIt's not a good policy, because the road surface is dreadful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.27,0:10:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小孩子可不擅长修路\NBabies are no good at building roads, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.57,0:10:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费雪牌土路是沿陡山修建的\NAlong with the Fisher Price road there's steep hills.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.57,0:10:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,60)}(Fisher Price 费雪 美国儿童玩具品牌)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.08,0:10:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对哈蒙德那台笨重的卡车来说 是个问题\NWhich were a problem for Hammond's heavy lumber bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.00,0:10:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上帝啊 太折磨人了\NGod, it's torture.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.00,0:10:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我恨这里 我恨这里 我恨这里\NI hate this, I hate this, I hate this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.86,0:10:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,换档 不对\NChange gear... No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.70,0:11:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不停地打齿\NGrind, grind, grind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.00,0:11:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等我们到达目的地了\NAnd when we get to the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.25,0:11:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们还要在桂河上修一座桥\Nwe have to build a bridge over the River Kwai.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.69,0:11:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最终 我们不得不放松下疲惫的筋骨\NEventually, we had to rest our weary bones,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.00,0:11:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们把车子停在了一个偏远山区的休息站\Nso we pulled over in a remote settlement.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.26,0:11:23.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许这种地方的村民\NYou know, in a village like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.15,0:11:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,压根就不知道西方世界的存在\Nit really is possible they don't know the West exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.00,0:11:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他们也许从未见过我们这样的面孔 -是的\NThey will never have seen faces like ours. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.58,0:11:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我惊讶他们居然没有被吓到\NI'm amazed they're not more amazed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.18,0:11:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想应该是文化代沟 表现出来可能很粗鲁\NI think it's a cultural thing, it would be rude to show it. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.38,0:11:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有点类似于...\NIt's sort of...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.75,0:11:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们绝对是他们见到的第一批白种人\NDefinitely the first white faces they've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.00,0:11:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在距离他们身后很远的后方\NMany miles further back,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.70,0:11:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我用了一个绑带\NI had sorted my axle issue
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.36,0:11:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,解决了前轴错位的问题\Nby using a ratchet strap to hold it in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.81,0:11:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我恨我的卡车\NI hate my lorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.33,0:12:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在驾驶的只是个大狗蛋 背上还有一个起重机\NWhat I'm driving here is a massive dog's egg with a crane on the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.37,0:12:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上帝啊 赶快结束这一切吧\NOh, God, let this day end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.60,0:12:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随着太阳的逐渐西下 我赶上了我的同事们\NAs the afternoon sun drew low, I was reunited with my colleagues,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.74,0:12:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们决定在一座小镇露营\Nand we decided to make camp in a small town.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.08,0:12:23.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看那个地方 露天公共天然浴场\NLook at that lot. Communal, open-air natural bathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.93,0:12:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.00,0:12:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们身处掸邦\NWe're in the middle of the Shan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.36,0:12:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们本来应该怕的要死\NWe're supposed to be frightened to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.31,0:12:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但其实一点都不吓人 一切都很美好\NIt's not frightening though, is it? It's lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.64,0:12:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们搭帐篷的时候 当地人看上去也忙了起来\NAs we set up camp, the locals seemed to be busy as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.22,0:12:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杰里米找到了原因\NAnd Jeremy had found out why.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.64,0:12:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-哈蒙德 梅  -干啥\NHammond, May. Yes? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.44,0:13:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看上去有人想请我们去参加聚会\NIt turns out we've been invited to a party.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.88,0:13:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-好吧 -哪里 -这里 就在镇上\NRight. Where? Here, in the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.58,0:13:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道这里一直处于内战当中\NYou know there's been a civil war raging?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.31,0:13:12.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今晚所有参加过战争的人都会来到这里\NAll of the people who've been fighting are coming together tonight
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.87,0:13:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欢迎我们来到掸邦\Nto welcome us here to the Shan state.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.00,0:13:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道签署北爱和平协议的时候 他们让\NYou know the Good Friday Agreement where they got Major,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.00,0:13:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gerry Adams 和Paisley共处一室多么令人惊奇吗\NGerry Adams and Paisley all in one room and it was amazing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.57,0:13:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,显然 在缅甸咱仨同样让人感到惊奇\NWell, apparently this is as amazing as that in Burma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.00,0:13:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他们认为我们是什么人 -我不清楚\NWho do they think we are? What? Look I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.10,0:13:33.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,60)}(均为英国政府高官)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.10,0:13:33.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许是理查德·Dimbleby, 詹姆斯·McNulty和杰里米·Paxman\NProbably Richard Dimbleby, James McNulty and Jeremy Paxman.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.16,0:13:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他们没听说过TopGear吧 -显然没\NThey're not familiar with Top Gear, are they? Evidently not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.64,0:13:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唯一让我疑惑的就是\NThe only thing I'm speculating on
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.80,0:13:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认为咱不应该穿成这样出席\Nis I don't think we should turn up looking like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.16,0:13:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不要吧 我没带正装出来\NNo. I have no formal wear with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.54,0:13:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,光着也比这强\NNaked would be better than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.89,0:13:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由于哈蒙德不让我们使用他的浴室\NAs Hammond wouldn't let us use his shower,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.24,0:13:54.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,詹姆斯和我开始寻求当地人的帮助\NJames and I had to go native.'
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.19,0:14:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很棒的水利系统啊\NThis's a brilliant system they got here
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.20,0:14:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,女人去那边 男人来这边\NWomen go there, and men go here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.67,0:14:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们完成了沐浴之后\NAs we finished our ablutions...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.15,0:14:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各方代表开始抵达现场\Nthe various factions started to arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.00,0:14:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杰里米邀请我们去喝餐前鸡尾酒\NAnd Jeremy invited us over for pre-dinner cocktails.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.23,0:14:33.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们随意喝吧 因为我有一个想法\NListen, help yourselves to a drink, because I've had a thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.00,0:14:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很可能军情六处或者美国缉毒局什么的\NIt's possible MI6 or the DEA or some intelligence agency
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.00,0:14:44.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-想要从我们口中得出一些关于这里的情报 -是的\Nwill want to talk to us when we get back about here. Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.00,0:14:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们要注意大英帝国的形象 我们代表着BBC\NSo, manners - polite, British, representatives of the BBC,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.86,0:14:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是要小心\Nbut pay attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.20,0:14:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在你到处张望的时候 动作别太明显 自然点...\NBut don't make it obvious that you're finding things out, just be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.56,0:14:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最后一句给哈蒙德的警告就是\NWith a final word of warning to Hammond...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.12,0:14:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别喝大了\NDon't get drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.08,0:14:59.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我走之前再来一杯\NI'll just have one before I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.66,0:15:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-然后我们就去参加派对了\N..we headed off to the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.30,0:15:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来自大英帝国的BBC电视台\NFrom Britain, BBC television.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.58,0:15:10.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,派对上为我们提供了一些当地美食\N'Where we were offered some local delicacies...'
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.31,0:15:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这...是毛毛虫\NDoes it. Oh, it's a caterpillar?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.12,0:15:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对 就是传说中的毛毛虫\NThat's right, that's right, caterpillar. Caterpillar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.40,0:15:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毛毛虫走好\NGoodbye, caterpillar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.44,0:15:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看来毛毛虫不对哈蒙德的胃口\N'As caterpillars weren't to Hammond's taste,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.82,0:15:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他去找对胃口的了\N'he went off to find something that was.'
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.29,0:15:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好你好 喝酒没问题\NHello, hello. Hello, yes. I can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.72,0:15:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来 干杯\NYes, I could do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.98,0:15:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看起来不错哦 加一个 这节奏不错\NThis is all right. I'm coming in, I like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.00,0:15:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随着上的菜越来越多\N'As the food kept coming...'
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.00,0:15:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是禅 这是蟋蟀\NThis is a cicada, a cricket.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.00,0:15:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我发现当地那特殊的作物\N'..I was discovering that the region's special agriculture
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.00,0:15:45.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也没有那么神秘\N'didn't seem to be that special.'
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.37,0:15:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-主要是葵花籽 大豆 就这些? -没别的了\NSo it's sunflower seeds, soya bean, nothing else. Nothing, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.00,0:15:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过要比涨姿势\N'Still, I was learning more than James...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.37,0:16:01.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我强多了\N'..or Hammond.'
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.38,0:16:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁还有威士忌?苏格兰威士忌吗?\N-Who's got any Whiskey? -Have you got any Scotch?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.23,0:16:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到午夜时分 我已经熟悉了当地的每一种作物了\N'By midnight, I'd been through every single crop in the area.'
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.22,0:16:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,芝麻种子 是的 还有玉米\NSesame seeds. Sesame seeds, yeah, yeah. Maize.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.00,0:16:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,于是我也向哈蒙德学习\N'So, I took a leaf out of Hammond's book...'
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.00,0:16:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,干杯 干杯\NCheers, cheers, cheers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.00,0:16:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与詹姆斯以及剧组一半人 嗨起来了\N'..and, along with May and half the film crew, joined the party.'
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.64,0:16:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我穿着犀利 我表情炫酷\NI'm dressing sharp and I'm acting cool,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.57,0:16:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,啦啦队长就在此\NGot a cheerleader here...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.16,0:17:14.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过有一点是肯定的\NWell, one thing is for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.60,0:17:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,缅甸的这个区域是绝对没有毒品的\NThere are absolutely no drugs in this part of Burma. No, none.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.56,0:17:20.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一点都没 我所有人都问过了\NAbsolutely no I talked to everybody and...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.19,0:17:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我问过那些那些卖文具的商贩\NI talked to people involved in the sales and distribution of stationery,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.00,0:17:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我问过农民 军人和库尔茨上校\NI talked to farmers, Army people, Colonel Kurtz.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.56,0:17:31.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也问过库尔茨上校 他当时喝高了\NI spoke to Colonel Kurtz, he was in vegetables.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.09,0:17:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果回去后军情六处问话\NSo if MI6 talks to us when we get back
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.59,0:17:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以说 你们找错地方了\Nwe can say, "You're looking in the wrong place."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.79,0:17:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看到没 哈蒙德同志不行了\NHave you seen... Our colleague is not well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.78,0:17:50.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等那二货完全清醒能开车 要很久啊\NWe've got a lot of time to kill this morning before that is capable of driving a lorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.78,0:18:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,许多许多小时之后 我们重新上路了\N'Many, many hours later, we were back on the road.'
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.15,0:18:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,昨晚玩脱了\NLast night might got out of hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.00,0:18:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我好像把那个上校打了一拳\NI think I punched a colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.63,0:18:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或者是和他接吻了\NOr kissed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.91,0:18:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-哈蒙德 -啥\NHammond? Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.19,0:18:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再说一遍你喝得威士忌叫啥名字\NWhat was your whiskey called again?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.81,0:18:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,60)}(亨基·巴尼斯特 苏格兰著名威士忌)
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.81,0:18:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亨基·巴尼斯特\NHankey Bannister
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.61,0:18:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亨基·巴尼斯特 缅北第三好的威士忌\N"Hankie Banister. Third-best Whiskey in northern Burma."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.00,0:18:31.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而不久 我们记忆中"现代启示录"结尾般那样的夜晚\N'Soon, though, the memories of our night at the end of Apocalypse Now
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.80,0:18:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被这世外桃源似的美景所取代了\N'were eclipsed by the sheer beauty of this untouched paradise.'
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.00,0:18:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一生中从来没有照过这么多的风景照\NI've never taken more landscape photographs in my entire life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.19,0:18:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,简直\NIt's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.12,0:18:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不看看这样的美景你们的人生就不完整\NYou've got to come here. You have got to come and see this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.40,0:19:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,詹姆斯也应该能欣赏这美景的\N'James would have enjoyed the view, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.56,0:19:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是预料之中的 他的车又跪了\N'but predictably he'd had yet another breakdown.'
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.53,0:19:16.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,擦\NCock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.94,0:19:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次的问题是 好吧 其实我也不知道\NThe problem is - well, I don't know what the problem is,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.89,0:19:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但从爬坡开始没劲了\Nbut I started losing power up the hill
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.31,0:19:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后挂不上三档\Nthen it would not even drive in third
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.22,0:19:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后感觉只有俩气缸在工作\Nthen it felt like has started running on two,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.97,0:19:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后肯定就一个了\Nthen it was definitely only running on one cylinder,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.88,0:19:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为听起来就和夜用发电机一个德行\Nbecause it sounded like the sort of generator people put on in the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.88,0:19:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,BBC2台禁词\NNon-BBC Two word.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.53,0:19:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我解决好喷油嘴的故障以后\N'Once I'd fixed the problem, which was wonky fuel injectors,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.81,0:19:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我再次踏上了征程\N'I was on the move again.'
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.58,0:19:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这货车真是稀烂的够可以了\NGod, this lorry is appalling.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.01,0:19:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不一会儿我就赶上他们了\N'And it didn't take long to catch the others,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.04,0:19:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为山路太陡\N'because the road was steep,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.93,0:19:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而哈蒙德又是在最前面\Nand Hammond was in front.'
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.51,0:20:04.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一档 情况不妙\NFirst gear. Bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.00,0:20:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有史以来开的最慢的一次\NLiterally the slowest I've ever been.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.74,0:20:13.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈蒙德 再慢下去我就要憋熄火了\NHammond, I haven't got any more gears left.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.00,0:20:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我让不开啊 路太窄了\NI can't get out the way, the road's too narrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.00,0:20:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开着货车我可快不起来\NI can't go any faster, I'm in a lorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.95,0:20:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,简直就是垂直爬坡啊\NIt's pretty much vertical.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.11,0:20:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天呐 这尾气\NGod, look at the smoke now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.76,0:20:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我快得尘肺病了\NI've got a mining lung disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.85,0:20:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我开始yy哈蒙德被剥了皮以后的样子\NI'm starting to imagine what Hammond might look like without any skin on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.78,0:20:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,又是闹哪样\NNow what?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.76,0:20:50.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得我们都往后面倒一点 这辆车就过得去了\NI think if we all back up, he can come in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.00,0:20:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈蒙德 我们不能 这样解决不了问题\NHammond, we can't - there's nothing to be gained by...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.74,0:21:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈蒙德 你个蠢货 你把我的动感大货给撞了!\NHammond, you idiot, you've reversed into the sports lorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.00,0:21:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你把它弄坏了 -我没看到 真的是意外\N-You've broken it. -I didn't know. Genuinely, that was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.58,0:21:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有种你别走啊 哈蒙德 哈蒙德\NDon't just drive off, Hammond. Hammond! Hammond!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.06,0:21:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他撞坏了我的大灯 水箱和防撞杆 -我后视镜里看不到\N-He's broken my headlights, radiator. My bull bar is broken. -I couldn't see in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.20,0:21:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,啥 你就凭意识流在倒车\NWhat, you just reverse and hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.00,0:21:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你认为我的车在哪里 一整天我都跟在你后面\NWhere did you think I was?! All day, I have been
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.26,0:21:30.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没想到这么近\Nbehind you. I didn't think it was that close
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.23,0:21:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在明白为啥卡车司机要安那些杆子了\NI now know why they have those stickers for lorry drivers -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.53,0:21:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你看不到我的后视镜 我就看不见你\N"If you can't see my mirrors, I can't see you."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.20,0:21:41.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然严格讲我该为这次事故负责\N'Even though the incident had been technically my fault,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.29,0:21:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还是遵循了标准的解决方案\N'I still followed the standard procedure.'
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.75,0:21:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他懂规矩的 常在河边走 哪有...\NWhat? He knows the rules. Live by the sword, you must...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.00,0:21:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也记不起来了 反正就那意思 你们脑补一下\NI can't remember. Whatever. Something to do with swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.68,0:22:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在我前面堵了一天 然后又倒车来撞我\NHe held me up all day, then he reversed into me,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.20,0:22:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我觉得他另一只手腕会在今晚骨折\Nso I think tonight Hammond's other wrist might break.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.11,0:22:12.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而当我到达过夜点的时候\NHowever, when I reached the overnight holds,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.78,0:22:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我又想出了一个更邪恶的点子\NI came up with a more fiendish idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.29,0:22:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个点子和哈蒙德车上用来收集雨水洗澡\NAn idea that involved the bucket Hammond had fitted to collect
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.00,0:22:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,的那个桶有关\Nrainwater for his shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.07,0:22:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得足够报复他在路上把咱俩堵了一天的恶行\NThis does pay him back for holding us up all day long. Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.80,0:22:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-还有 -第二趴There was more. Part two
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.00,0:22:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随后我开始修理我卡车的冷却系统了\N'I then began to work on my lorry's waterworks.'
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.58,0:22:46.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这水箱的固定螺栓好粗 22毫米 是啊\NMassive nuts holding the radiator on. 22 millimetres. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.92,0:22:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 这水还是热的 新鲜的雨水\NIt's actually warm. So warm, fresh rainwater.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.00,0:22:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-黄金雨 -我能尝到上天的恩泽 在室外\NGolden rain. I can taste the goodness. The outdoors.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.25,0:23:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们两个都享受不了\NAnd neither of you two thought of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.56,0:23:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吃完烤蚂蚱晚餐后\N'After dining on roast grasshopper,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.00,0:23:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们晚上决定玩一下孔明灯\N'we spent the evening playing with my Chinese lanterns.'
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.47,0:23:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要在这放飞吗 为啥不行\NAre you going to set them off here? Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.00,0:23:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这个国家大多数人住的房子都是\NI should say in a country where a lot of people live in houses made of...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.79,0:23:31.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-都是啥 干草吗 -放心 没问题的\NWhat is it, dried grass? Oh, relax. That's not going to be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.82,0:23:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能放飞一个孔明灯的概率堪忧啊\NThe chances of you getting one of those things to work...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.56,0:23:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放手 飞起来吧\NLet go, let it fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.42,0:23:40.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦耶 哈蒙德\NYes. Hammond,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.84,0:23:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你错了 -飞向谷仓或者干草房顶吧\NGo find a barn or a thatched roof. ye of little faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.00,0:23:46.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要去拿瓶啤酒 好好回味这美妙的一刻\NNow, let's just... I'm going to get a beer and savour the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.40,0:23:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这就像是移动的篝火 -是的\N-Is it just a... It's a mobile bonfire. -It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.54,0:23:53.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,举个例子 如果这东西落到一片罂粟地里面\NIf it were to land in a field of poppies, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.49,0:23:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那场面会多么恢弘啊\Nimagine how beautiful that would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.77,0:23:59.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,心满意足后 我们睡觉去了\N'Feeling content and happy, we went to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.59,0:24:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 其实只有我\NWell, one of us did.'
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.00,0:24:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得有多大可能把他弄醒\NWhat do you think the chances are of waking him?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.07,0:24:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弄不醒的 他睡得跟死猪似的\NYou won't wake him, he sleeps the sleep of the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.00,0:24:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是空挡\NThat's in neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.46,0:24:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你大爷!\NJesus Christ!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.76,0:24:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,翌日早晨 尽管周围很宁静\Nthe next morning despite the tranquility of our surroundings
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.76,0:24:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杰瑞米骂骂咧咧的上路了\N'Jeremy hit the road in a fractious mood.'
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.90,0:24:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们为啥要把我从货车里面倒出来\NWhy did you tip me out of my lorry?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.02,0:24:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为你把我的帐篷吊起来了\NBecause you swung me around in my tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.59,0:24:57.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你活该 因为你太烦了 我一向很可爱\NWell you deserved that because you're irritating. I'm never irritating.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.54,0:25:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个观点还真是有理有据令人信服啊 我好内疚哦\NIt's a good point Jeremy raises, I feel quite bad about it now,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.32,0:25:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他上次犯贱是啥时候来着\Nbecause when has he ever been irritating?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.00,0:25:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更糟糕的是\N'To make my mood even worse,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.00,0:25:13.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,持续高强度驾驶对我的刹车造成了严重的影响\N'the endless hard going had had a catastrophic effect on my brakes.'
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.07,0:25:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得只有左边的刹车在工作\NI think they're only working now on the left-hand side.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.89,0:25:19.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有还是没有\NNothing, everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.60,0:25:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只在那一瞬间 刹车突变太厉害了\NYou move your foot that much, that's the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.89,0:25:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幸运的是 我们离缅泰边境只有80英里了\NFortunately, we were now only 80 miles from the border with Thailand.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.92,0:25:34.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是不幸的是 这80英里一点都不舒服\NBut, unfortunately, none of those miles would be gentle.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.00,0:25:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 我这里很颠 杰瑞米那肯定更糟\NOh, it's bad in here and it will be worse in Jeremy's lorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.47,0:25:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,又不舒服又热 简直要疯了\N'It was desperately uncomfortable, and hot,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.00,0:26:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前面就是最大的山脉\N'and ahead of us lay the biggest mountain range yet.'
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.51,0:26:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开着水箱破损的卡车爬这种坡真是作死\NThis climb is exactly what you need in a lorry with a leaky radiator.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.00,0:26:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,擦 这落差真是吓尿啊\NOh, that is a trouser-threatening drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.55,0:26:39.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,詹姆斯梅是一个恐高的男人\NJames May is a man who does not like heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.79,0:26:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且他的车前轴就是几根线固定的\NHe is also a man whose lorry has its front axle held on with a bit of string.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.24,0:26:50.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-梅 你觉得眩晕吗 -我没往下看\N-How's your vertigo, May? -I'm not looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.57,0:26:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但真是谢谢提醒啊\NBut thanks for reminding me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.39,0:26:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们如龟速一般前行\N'Progress was extremely slow
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.25,0:27:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我必须不时停下来加水\N'as I had to keep stopping to refill my radiator.'
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.78,0:27:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是从环氧胶那儿漏的\NPouring out from exactly where the araldite was.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.00,0:27:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得这是一个很不靠谱的方法 但还是试试吧\NFairly convinced this is an old wives' tale, but we shall see.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.00,0:27:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与此同时 詹姆斯的车今天第一次罢工了\N'Meanwhile, James was having his first breakdown of the day.'
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.00,0:27:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不对\NNope.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.00,0:27:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这一次是分动器的问题\N'This time, it was the transfer box,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.59,0:27:33.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,分动器失去固定了\N'which had burst free from its mountings.'
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.85,0:27:38.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是分动器 这是分动器固定的架子\NThat's the transfer box, that's the bracket where it's bolted on,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.11,0:27:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这两个螺栓被甩出来了\Nthose two bolts have been shaken out.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.72,0:27:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我擦\NOh, cock.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.91,0:27:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还在爬升 绵延不绝\NStill going on, still more mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.00,0:27:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,啥时候是个头啊\NWhen will this end?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.59,0:28:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的天 越来越陡了\NOh, my God, it gets steep.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.08,0:28:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我必须不断前进\NI've got to keep moving,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.30,0:28:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一旦停车后再起步 离合器就跪了\Nif I stop, pulling away will\Nkill the clutch, I'm sure of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.40,0:28:13.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在 我的发动机温度快爆表了\NOK, my temperature gauge is now really very high.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.69,0:28:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得找条小溪\NI am looking for a little stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.96,0:28:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而 我们的情况要比\NStill, at least the mood was more cheerful than it
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.60,0:28:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后续部队好多了\Nwas at the back of the convoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.48,0:28:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,二挡没了 发动机...\NBLEEPING second gear failed, and now the engine has BLEEP BLEEP arse.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.51,0:28:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你个废物\NYou piece of BLEEP.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.61,0:28:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在精心养护之后 杰里米和我终于到达了山顶\NWith some careful nursing,\NJeremy and I eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.00,0:28:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,收获了累累硕果\Nreached the summit, where there was\None hell of a reward.'
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.30,0:29:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太美了\NThat is insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.62,0:29:17.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从未见过如此美景\NNever seen views like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.91,0:29:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如此开阔 不可能同时见到这么多\NNot as extensive. Not all at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.36,0:29:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你都能从中看到什么 喜马拉雅的山\NWhat have we got here? Himalayas.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.59,0:29:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥地利\NYeah. Austria.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.53,0:29:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,隐约的苏格兰 一点点 还有这蓝天白云\NBit of Scotland going on there. Quite a bit of Scotland. And the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.30,0:29:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一望无际啊 就像德克萨斯的天一样\NEnormous. Like a sky from Texas.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.10,0:29:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,德州的天 但比德州更大 大多了\NTexas sky. But bigger. Much bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.25,0:29:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美呆了\NAbsolutely staggering.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.60,0:29:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可惜 这美好的一颗很快被打破了\N'Sadly, though, the piece of the moment was then shattered.'
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.04,0:29:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,梅的小拖车驾到\NThe A-MAY van has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.06,0:29:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,感觉他还在气头上\NHe's in a rile.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.00,0:30:05.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说 你的起重机修好了\NMate, you've got the crane here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.70,0:30:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我擦勒 你个XX\NBLEEP! Heap of dog BLEEP!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.28,0:30:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你敢多说一句试试\NDon't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.08,0:30:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道佛教的一句老话吗\NYou know the old Buddhist expression, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.71,0:30:20.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,翻我下车之人必将抛锚无数\NHe who tips a man out of his lorry will suffer from many breakdowns.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.64,0:30:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从这里到缅泰边界 是一路下坡\NFrom here to the border with Thailand it was downhill all the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.31,0:30:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这对于我来说 可谓是惊心动魄\NWhich for me, at least, was a bit alarming.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.03,0:30:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天呐 看这路\NOh, God. Look at that road now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.76,0:30:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没刹车 一点都没有\NNo brakes, no brakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.29,0:30:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你制动彻底报废 还怎么混\NIf your brakes went entirely would you stay with it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.83,0:30:45.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,修车还是跳车\Nand hope you could sort it out or would you bail out?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.39,0:30:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不瞒你说 我现在正想这事\NI'm actually sitting here planning that very thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.45,0:30:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已经准备好跳车了\NI've planned my bailout already.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.57,0:30:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我练了好几遍抓门把手的动作\NI've even practised lunging for the door handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.85,0:31:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在都能想象出詹姆斯\NI've got an image of James punching his lorry all
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.57,0:31:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在坠崖时在车里挣扎的画面\Nthe way down the slopes as they fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.18,0:31:17.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出乎意料的是 我们都安全下山\NAmazingly, we all made it to the bottom of the mountain in one piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.77,0:31:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,基本安全\NNearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.51,0:31:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在我们离缅泰边境只剩下60多公里了\NAnd now we were only 40 miles from the Thai border.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.80,0:31:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是这里 我们正离开缅甸\NOh, this is it. We are about to leave Burma.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.41,0:31:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会怀念她的\NI'm gonna miss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.17,0:32:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不久我们跨过边境进入了泰国\NSoon we cross the border into Thailand and this meant
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.41,0:32:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这也意味着我们离终点桂河只有30公里了\Nwe were now just 19 miles from our finishing line at the River Kwai.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.06,0:32:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,30公里完好的铺装道路\N19 miles of easy-going on smooth roads.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.48,0:32:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,啊 哈蒙德 你的轮胎\NOh, it's hammered your tyre! Your tyre is...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.71,0:32:42.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你轮胎爆了 哥们\NIt's detonating, mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.15,0:32:46.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很难跟你解释\NIt's hard to explain to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.73,0:32:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会放弃 不会停车 少个轮子能怎样\NI'm not giving up. I'm not stopping. How many wheels do I need?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.70,0:33:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幸运的是 我剩下的胎没爆 随着夜幕降临\NHappily, the rest of my tyres stayed inflated and as darkness fell...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.61,0:33:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们终于到达了终点\N..we finally reached our destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.29,0:33:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们觉得桂河就在身边\NI believe we are at the River Kwai.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.76,0:33:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各位 我的起重机还在\NThe crane is here, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.13,0:33:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然载着它的是一辆破车 随便啦\NIt's bolted onto a BLEEP lorry but never mind that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.43,0:33:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我脑袋已经麻木了\NMy brain is frazzled.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.03,0:33:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在满身是汗\NOh I'm sweating here
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.57,0:33:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我再也不想听这卡车爬坡时发出各种怪声\Nand I don't wanna listen to the lorry struggling and screaming and straining to climb another hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.56,0:33:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我这个世纪都不想起床了\NI am going to sleep for 1,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.76,0:33:50.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我脊椎有没有从头顶捅出来\NHas my spine come out of the top of my head?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.83,0:33:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我都看不见 因为我的眼珠晃丢了\NI can't see because my eyes have been shaken loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.55,0:33:55.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得我的胯脱臼了\NI think my pelvis has moved around in my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.97,0:33:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不奇怪 就你那破车 -都不能动了\NI'm not surprised in your lorry. It doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.52,0:34:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的踏板都是错位的 你的也是\NCause your pedals are all different. You've got that haven't you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.47,0:34:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,松离合要这样\NReleasing the clutch is that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.90,0:34:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每次都搞得我跟入了共济会似的\NIt's like a Masonic dance thing that I have to do every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.70,0:34:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道健身房那种天杀的力量盘么\NYou know those power plates in gyms that make you stupid?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.43,0:34:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在有严重的心理阴影\NThere's also a psychological thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.03,0:34:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每次听到柴油机启动的声音就会神经过敏\Nevery time I hear a diesel engine start I have a nervous twitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.74,0:34:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有手动变速箱 什么\NManual gearboxes. What?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.01,0:34:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你已经让我痛不欲生了\NYou have ruined me and my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.77,0:34:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,换挡杆离我太远\NThe gearbox is too far...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.82,0:34:31.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当年战犯是步行去桂河造桥\N"The Prisoners Of War walked to their bridge site,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.22,0:34:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们还开着车就别抱怨了\N"you have driven here so shut up."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.00,0:34:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-造桥工作明早五点准时开始 -什么\N"Work on the bridge starts at 0500." What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.74,0:34:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且只有三辆卡车全部通过桥体\N"0500 and you can't go home
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.69,0:34:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们才能回家\N"until all three lorries have driven over it."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.21,0:34:54.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-早上五点 -有意义么 我们又不是在打仗\N0500. What's the point? We're not actually still in the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.44,0:34:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-为什么非要那么早 -不就是一条小河嘛\NWhat's the point of 0500? It will only be a little river.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.25,0:35:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第二天早上五点 过了十一分钟\NThe next morning at precisely 0500.. and 11,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.74,0:35:09.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们发现了自己的无知\Nwe discovered just how wrong we were.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.64,0:35:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它比我想象的宽多了\NIt is much wider than I thought it was going to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.86,0:35:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我以为就一水沟 -我也是 -实际却宽一百倍\NI thought it would be a comedic gully. I did. It's 100 times wider.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.03,0:35:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要造一座60米长的桥\NWe were going to need a 60m bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.81,0:35:42.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以詹姆斯负责去做计划\Nso James went off to make plans
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.35,0:35:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而哈蒙德和我则决定去测水深\Nand Hammond and I decided to measure the depth of the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.30,0:35:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,呃 我说的是我们俩\NWell, when I say Hammond and I...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.11,0:35:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,水已经很深了\NI'm approaching plumb depth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.00,0:35:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,进入深水区 啊\NAh! Broach the plumb... Oh! Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.52,0:36:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这水怎么这么凉\NIt's ever so cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.20,0:36:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不想干这活\NI hate my job!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.00,0:36:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你见过亚力克·基尼斯在桂河大桥里喊\NIn Bridge On The River Kwai did Alec Guinness go,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.89,0:36:07.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这水怎么这么凉么\N"Oh, it's ever so cold!"
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.19,0:36:10.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真下水的时候他肯定也这反应\NI bet he did in reality. Oh! I bet he did in reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.76,0:36:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这时 我的同事不幸被水流冲走了\NOh! Sadly, at this point my colleague was carried away by the current.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.00,0:36:19.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,慢慢游\NSwim, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.62,0:36:20.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我游着呢\NI am!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.77,0:36:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是全世界最烂的泳将\NYou're the weakest swimmer in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.00,0:36:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鉴于他提供不了任何有价值的信息\NAnd since he was providing no useful feedback,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.38,0:36:30.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只好去检查詹姆斯的计划\NI went to check on James's plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.00,0:36:32.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是这么想的\NThis is what I was thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.67,0:36:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两边是河岸\NThe bank goes down at each side obviously,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.59,0:36:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们用成筐的石头先做个平台\Nwe build up the approach area with these baskets of stones,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.94,0:36:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后用竹子来做些直立的桥墩\Nmake vertical piles out of bamboo like this, these longerons
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.65,0:36:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些我管它叫桥面 是用竹子绑在一起的\NI'm calling them, they are bamboo lashed together,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.51,0:36:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样横在上面\Nthese will go this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.71,0:36:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为车轮搭两溜 中间不用铺\NTwo tracks for the wheels, the rest is immaterial
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.32,0:36:53.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后上面再搞个这样的结构\Nand then a superstructure like this
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.76,0:36:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,增加承重\Nall adding strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.04,0:36:59.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道 就跟电影里面那个一样\NYou know the sort of thing so that it looks a bit like the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.00,0:37:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总而言之我们得先有石头\NBasically we need to start with rocks
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.27,0:37:04.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后搞点铁丝网做盒子把它们装进去\Nand some wire mesh to make boxes to put them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.36,0:37:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上哪去弄石头\NWhere are we getting rocks from?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.00,0:37:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那归你管 你的是翻斗卡车\NThat's your job because you have the tipper lorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.83,0:37:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我开始着手做铁丝网盒子\NI set about making the wire mesh baskets,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.07,0:37:17.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,顺便清空了杰里米的翻斗\Nfreed up the space in Jeremy's cargo bay...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.49,0:37:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,梅 我跟你没完\NMay, you imbecile!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.00,0:37:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当哈蒙德回来的时候\NAnd when Hammond finally returned,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.00,0:37:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我让他俩一块去附近的采石场拉石头\NI sent them both off to a nearby quarry to get the rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.80,0:37:33.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把石头往这车的前一放\NYou've put them in the front of this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.32,0:37:35.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对 尽量往前放\NYeah, stick them in the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.29,0:37:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,剩下的放这边\NLet's have these ones here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.27,0:37:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杰里米 你能搭把手么\NJeremy... Are you going to do anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.00,0:37:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要干嘛 帮着装车啊 他不是在装嘛\NWhat can I do? Load the trucks. He's loading them!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.05,0:37:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,石头装好了以后 杰里米终于起床了\NWith the trucks loaded, Jeremy finally got off his backside
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.86,0:37:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但随即就开始对我大吼\Nand immediately started to shout at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.00,0:38:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈蒙德 你个白痴\NHammond! You idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.55,0:38:01.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.11,0:38:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你给我装了400吨石头 车陷下去了\NYou put about 400 tonnes of rocks and it is stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.89,0:38:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我专门把你叫醒 让你帮忙装车\NI woke you to say are you going to help with the loading?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.93,0:38:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的原话是 有人装就行了\NYour words were, "There's the man doing!"
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.28,0:38:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不管我也没办法\NThat's exactly the kind of issue you should have been awake for.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.67,0:38:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我怎么知道你车载重多少 没概念\NHow do I know what your load is? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.28,0:38:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在唯一的办法就是倒一些石头出来\NThe only solution was to tip some of the rocks out.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.74,0:38:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 不 不\NOh, no, no, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.43,0:38:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天呐 这可有的瞧了 你看\NOh, my. That's a remarkable accident. Look...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.95,0:38:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要啊\NOh, jeez, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.99,0:38:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的挡风玻璃都掉下来了\NYour windscreen has come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.97,0:38:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这简直就是灾难啊\NThis is a *** disaster now
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.36,0:38:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开起来倒挺凉快\NThe breeze will be nice(!)
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.09,0:38:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不出意料的是\NPredictably, when we got back,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.95,0:38:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,詹姆斯对我表达了满满的同情\NJames was overflowing with sympathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.47,0:39:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你是用头撞的吗 -是这样的...\NDid you head-butt it? But look...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.32,0:39:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,理查德和詹姆斯开始亲手动卸车\NRichard and James began to load their basket by hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.00,0:39:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这石头可够沉的\NOh, that's a big rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.52,0:39:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但人和动物的区别在于 人会使用工具\NBut I'm allergic to manual labour so I used horsepower instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.36,0:39:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随后我就进城采购晚饭去了\NAnd then I went into town to buy supper.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.25,0:39:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是西葫芦吗\NIs this a marrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.80,0:39:40.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,啥 这是\NA...? Name...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.00,0:39:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是 这里居然这么叫 我原以为这是西葫芦\NThis is... Crikey, is it? I thought it was a marrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.37,0:39:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长见识了吧 在泰国西葫芦叫 对就叫那个\NThat's something you learn. In Thailand, the word for... Yes, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.83,0:39:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,西葫芦就叫 那个\NThat's the word for marrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.44,0:39:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回工地的时候 我招募了一群当地民工随我一起\NWhen I returned, I brought with me a gang of local labourers.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.46,0:40:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你都做了什么\NWhat are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.00,0:40:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是不可能独立建成这座桥的好吗\NThere's no way we're going to be able to build this bridge by ourselves, let's be reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.00,0:40:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说的没错 哈蒙德\NHe's right, Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.00,0:40:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,单靠咱们俩是不可能完成的\NYou and I are not going to be able to build this bridge by ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.23,0:40:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他要还这德行肯定没戏 -拜托 长官不干活好吗\NI know. Which is the way is was go. Hello, officers won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.26,0:40:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亚力克·基尼斯在"桂河大桥"里说的很清楚\NAlec Guinness made that very plain in Bridge On The River Kwai in the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.68,0:40:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,整部电影前提就是"长官不用干活"\NThat was the whole premise of the story is that officers won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.00,0:40:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你长官? -当然了\NYou're an officer? Of course I'm an officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.00,0:40:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-谁说你是的 -我明显就是 我天生男主命\NWho says you are an officer? I am, I am the Alec Guinness figure here. It's obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.79,0:40:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-就因为你有根破棒子 -你可看好你的棒子了\NBecause you've got a stick. That stick may disappear quite soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.70,0:40:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有了当地人的帮助 我和詹姆斯也开始有了起色\NWith the local chaps helping, James and I started to make good progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.61,0:41:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但正当我们辛勤工作的时候\NHowever, as we toiled away,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.40,0:41:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那位自封的长官却好像玩起了过家家\Nthe self-appointed officer seemed to be setting up a children's tea party.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.58,0:41:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你这又是在干嘛\NWhat are you doing now?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.44,0:41:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我跟19世纪在缅甸的英国人学了一招\NWell, it's a trick I learnt actually from the British in Burma in the 19th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.09,0:41:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会雇一个当地小孩 给他涂满果酱\Nthey would employ some local young chap, cover him in jam,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.58,0:41:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后他整天跟在身边 来吸引昆虫\Nhe would follow them around all day and he'd attract the insects.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.00,0:41:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们管他叫小酱\NThey called him a jam boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.00,0:41:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这是我的熊酱 -有点不人道吧\NThis is my jam bear. It doesn't seem very fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.58,0:41:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一点也不 因为果酱最后都归他了\NIt was, it was because at the end of the day he got to keep the jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.00,0:41:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,劳累了一天以后 我为大家奉上了可口的晚餐\NAt the end of our long difficult day, I produced my delicious supper.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.82,0:41:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,闻着蛮香的啊 用什么做的\NIt smells very good, Clarkson, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.77,0:41:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得悄悄跟你说\NMm, I'll whisper it to you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.58,0:41:53.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为不能让观众听到\Nbecause I can't say it in front of the viewers.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.00,0:41:57.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你再说一遍 她就盯着我说\NWhat? She just looked at me and went...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.61,0:42:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么说的 别激动\NWhat did you say? Steady on!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.54,0:42:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还为哈蒙德特意准备了点心\NI'd even prepared a treat for Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.46,0:42:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我还给你准备了特别的餐后点心 -什么\NFor after deserts I've got you something very special indeed. What?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.16,0:42:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我知道你喜欢Black Cock -没错\NI know you're partial to a bit of Black Cock. Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.00,0:42:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我给你搞来了\NAnd so I've managed to find...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.67,0:42:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你太伟大了\NOh, you hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.00,0:42:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-厉害 -直接喝? -那必须的\NOh, well done. Black Cock. Stiff one? Yes, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.00,0:42:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-有本事就一口闷 -干杯\NGet that down your neck. Cheers.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.90,0:42:28.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我干了\NBottoms up.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.00,0:42:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我跟你说 我今晚上要睡到死\NI'll tell you what, I'm going to sleep tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.27,0:42:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真的 累惨了\NAbsolutely. I am worn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.67,0:42:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第二天一早 等天亮了\NThe next morning, the dawn light reveals
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.33,0:42:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们才发现进度之慢\Njust how little we had achieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.00,0:42:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以没等晨雾散去 大家就都忙活起来了\NSo, before the morning mist had cleared, everyone was hard at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.85,0:42:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然了 大家并不包括\NWell, when I say everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.56,0:43:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-早啊 梅 -早\NMorning, May. Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.55,0:43:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你今天到底打不打算干活\NAre you actually going to do any work today?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.00,0:43:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我嘴皮都磨破了 你怎么还不懂\NI have explained this to you until I'm blue in the face.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.36,0:43:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长官不用干活\NOfficers won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.00,0:43:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喂!\NGuys!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.53,0:43:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,梅\NMay?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.84,0:43:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你听什么了吗\NCan you hear something?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.80,0:43:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我内急\NI need a poo!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.00,0:43:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,伙计们 我想清楚了 长官也可以干活\NGuys, I've had a thought. It turns out officers will work.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.26,0:43:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,释放了我之后\NAfter they released me...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.67,0:44:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-好吧 干活 -不老实还关你\NRight, work. Remains available.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.43,0:44:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我立即决定我们需要更多的机器来帮忙\NI immediately decided we needed more labour-saving machinery
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.00,0:44:07.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,于是就租了台挖掘机给哈蒙德\Nso I rented a digger for Hammond
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.39,0:44:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而我的选择会把船长虐出翔\Nand I went for something that would humiliate May.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.30,0:44:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恐怕詹姆斯把他的起重机开来是白费力了\NI'm afraid James has totally wasted his time bringing that crane here.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.00,0:44:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大猩猩!\NClarkson!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.00,0:44:33.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坏了\NOh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.59,0:44:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这都是啥 -它自己翻了詹姆斯 -你都干了什么\NWhat was that? It fell over, James. What have you done?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.27,0:44:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你先等会 你看见你的悬臂砸哪了吗\NHold on a minute! Did you see where the end of your jib landed?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.52,0:44:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是为了看桥墩在哪才撤了一步\NI had only walked back to see where the pile was.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.64,0:44:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要是我还站那的话 我脑袋就被敲掉了\NIf I'd still been standing there, it would have taken my head off!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.14,0:45:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-它翻倒了 -差点弄死我\NIt fell over! It almost killed me!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.00,0:45:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,翻倒了?起重机根本不可能自己翻好吗\NWhat do you mean, "It fell over"? They don't fall over, crane lorries!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.37,0:45:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大马路上怎么没见倒啊\NThey don't fall over on the motorway!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.02,0:45:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么叫不可能自己翻倒\NWhat do you mean, it doesn't fall over?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.13,0:45:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你故意弄翻的 -你的起重机太小了\NYou knocked it over! Your crane is too small,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.41,0:45:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我弄了辆更大的方便伸到河面上\Nso, I've got a bigger one to reach further into the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.21,0:45:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就算我起重机太小了 那也罪不至死吧\NRight. My crane is too small. That's punishable by death, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.15,0:45:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等詹姆斯冷静下来了以后 我们决定\NAfter James had calmed down a bit, we decided to solve the problem
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.00,0:45:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用理查德的挖掘机和梅的拖车 合力解决问题\Nby using the combined power of Richard's digger and the A-May Van.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.61,0:45:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,三 二 一\NIn three, two, one...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.46,0:45:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,起\NLift away!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.00,0:45:47.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢\NOh!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.73,0:45:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\NYeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.39,0:45:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,换了更结实线缆后 很快就把我的起重机扳正了\NBut, with stronger cables, we soon had my crane the right way up.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.00,0:45:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好 继续干活\NExcellent. And back to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.60,0:46:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把这个当大锤子用\NJust use this as an enormous hammer so...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.00,0:46:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,精工细活\NIt's all just delicacy, this.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.00,0:46:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他一路拖拉来的那辆小破车\NThat little insect that he's dragged all the way here
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.49,0:46:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根本就是碍我大事\Nis simply getting in our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.29,0:46:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好样的 哈蒙德\NOh, well done, Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.00,0:46:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么回事\NHang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.99,0:46:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-干得好! -哈蒙德 -拜托了詹姆斯 让一边去\NThat's the ticket! Hammond! Come on, James, out you come.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.73,0:46:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尖尖的东西\NSpiky things!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.08,0:46:50.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽管我们现在是团队合作\NEven though we were now working as a team,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.55,0:46:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大桥也开始成形\Nand the bridge was starting to take shape,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.95,0:46:56.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是远远落后于詹姆斯的计划\Nwe were still way behind James' schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.46,0:47:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这排蓝色柱子代表了我们现在应该达到的进度\NThis side, the blue pegs, represents how far we should have got by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.44,0:47:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,红色代表着我们已经达到的\NThe red pegs show how fa we actually have got.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.16,0:47:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,显然还不够\NObviously not far enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.64,0:47:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这比我想象的还慢\NIt's worse than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.96,0:47:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因此 我们三个人一起干到了半夜\NSo, the three of us worked on into the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.76,0:47:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这么长? -这么长\NThis long? This is long.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.00,0:47:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,递给哈蒙德\NThat's to go to Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.00,0:47:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喔 停 再来一点 我抓好了\NWhoa, stop there. A bit further. I've got it, I've got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.93,0:47:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而尽管我们上床时都已精疲力尽\NAnd even though we went to bed exhausted...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.74,0:47:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杰里米和我却根本睡不着\N..Sleep for Jeremy and I was impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.00,0:47:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大猩猩!\NClarkson!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.00,0:47:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好玩哈\NFunny!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.30,0:47:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我呵呵呵\NYou funny man!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.00,0:47:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们把他弄上岸时则更好玩\NWe were even funnier getting him back in.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.41,0:47:56.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-应该是这个红的吧 你说呢 -不知道\NI think it's the red one. Is it the red one? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.56,0:48:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧你坚持一下 这有一个圆圈\NRight, so, hang on, I've got one with, like, a circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.02,0:48:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个像洋葱似的\NThis one looks like an onion.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.91,0:48:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,转最底下那个\NThat bottom one swivels.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.25,0:48:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最底下那个!\NNo, the bottom one!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.63,0:48:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你从帐篷里面掉出来啦 詹姆斯\NJames, you're falling out your tent!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.85,0:48:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他掉水里去了\NHe's fallen in!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.22,0:48:17.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,救命\NHelp!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.97,0:48:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这个是闹钟啊 -对不住了 詹姆斯\NThat's an alarm clock, isn't it?! Oh, sorry, James!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.27,0:48:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这河底都是用便便堆起来的 -我知道\NThe bottom of this river's made out of turds. I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.00,0:48:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要呛太多水了\NYeah. Try not to drink more than a pint.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.46,0:48:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我随波逐流的时候\NAs I was carried away by the current,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.76,0:48:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我发现起重机现在已经够不到桥的末端了\NI noticed that the end of the bridge was now beyond the reach of our cranes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.00,0:48:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我上岸后 我们自制了一个打桩机\NSo when I returned, we built a home-made piledriver.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.32,0:48:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后把它安在自制的竹排上\NMounted it to a home-made barge...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.44,0:48:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后就开工了\NAnd kept right on going.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.48,0:48:55.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦不\NOh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.56,0:49:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抓住 把它停下来 詹姆斯\NGet it, stop it, stop it! James!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.30,0:49:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我够不着\NI can't stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.22,0:49:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下水\NGet it, get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.70,0:49:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的桥\NOur bridge! Our bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.00,0:49:17.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快点 别让它跑了 好几个小时的成果啊\NQuickly, go! Let's get it. Took hours！
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.00,0:49:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我抓住了\NI've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.00,0:49:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坚持住\NHold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.00,0:49:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 不\NNo! No!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.60,0:49:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这一脚可够深的 我陷进屎里了\NThat was a deep bit! I'm drowning in BLEEP!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.77,0:49:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人落水了\NMan overboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.20,0:49:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我怎么可能完成 太崩溃了\NHow the hell are we ever going to...? This is hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.00,0:49:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这可糟了\NThis is worse!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.63,0:49:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弃桥! 我得把这玩意弄回去\NAbandon bridge! I'm getting back...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.36,0:49:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上岸以后 我们召开了一个紧急会议\NOnce we were back ashore, we gathered for an emergency meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.84,0:49:58.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我估计应该是这其中一个坏掉了\NI presume it was one of these that gave way.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.11,0:50:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,桥墩 但为什么呢\NThe piling. But why did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.48,0:50:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,水流冲的呗\NCurrent.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.50,0:50:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说我们要是来一杯Hong Thong\NWould it help focus our minds more on the problem
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.08,0:50:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会不会更加专注一点呢\Nif we had a shot of Hong Thong?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.41,0:50:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好主意 或者来点red cock也行\NYes. Or we could have a Red Cock.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.00,0:50:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们还没试过Hong Thong\NWe haven't had Hong Thong.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.01,0:50:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有白酒吗\NYou got any white spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.00,0:50:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有\NYes, I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.00,0:50:19.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就不明白了\NI just don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.31,0:50:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要有一根桩子断了 就全完了\NIf one of the piers was wrong, that would do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.00,0:50:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果\NIf we used...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.59,0:50:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要是用那些一袋子一袋子的\NWhat if we used more of those whatever you call them, those bags of...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.00,0:50:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,咳咳就好了 如果我们多弄点成袋的石头\NIt's not helping him cough. What if we use more of those bags of stones
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.66,0:50:47.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来保护竹桩不被水流冲断呢\Nto protect the bamboo pillars from the current?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.26,0:50:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,顺便说一句 那白酒是纯酒精吧\NThat White Spirit, by the way, actually IS white spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.27,0:50:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你开玩笑吧 什么? -洗东西的酒精啊\NYou're kidding?! What? It's for cleaning brushes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.11,0:50:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们继续着大桥的搭建\N'We carried on with the build
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.77,0:51:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随着漫长酷热一天天过去\N'and as the long, hot days passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.18,0:51:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大桥也离对岸一天天近了\N'the bridge inched closer to the opposite bank.'
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.64,0:51:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,搞定\NThere you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.61,0:51:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 他直接把陂轧穿了\NOh! He's gone through the ramp.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.51,0:51:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁想要冰镇啤酒?\NWho here would like an ice cold beer?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.00,0:51:20.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,求你了 给点吧\NOh, yes, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.84,0:51:32.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但就当我们完成了2/3的进度时\N'But, as we passed the two thirds point,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.89,0:51:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我却被迫又召开了一次紧急会议\N'I was forced to call another emergency meeting.'
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.00,0:51:40.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了\NWhat's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.00,0:51:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还记得我们都认为\NWell, you know, we thought we were building a
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.15,0:51:45.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在桂河上面搭桥很厉害 是吗?\Nbridge over the River Kwai, which is noble?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.32,0:51:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-没错啊 -错了\NWe are. We're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.00,0:51:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这条河真正的名字\NThe name of that river...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.13,0:51:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,攻河?\NThe Kok?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.00,0:52:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Top Gear正在攻河上建一座桥\NTop Gear is building a bridge over the River Kok.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.00,0:52:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实很好记啊\NIt's actually memorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.70,0:52:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错 这样网上订电影就不会订错了\NIt is, you wouldn't order the wrong film from an Internet website.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.52,0:52:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你会非常小心 -BBC可该怎么介绍我们\NYou'd be very careful if you were. How is BBC presentation...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.23,0:52:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还记得每个节目前面那个女的吧\NYou know the woman at the beginning of every programme.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.40,0:52:19.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今晚 杰里米 詹姆斯和理查德三人在攻河上\N"And tonight, Jeremy, James and Richard build a bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.46,0:52:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,造了一座桥\N"over the River Kok"...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.80,0:52:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反正不能放弃啊\NWell, we're not moving it!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.91,0:52:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,此时此刻 我们的工作\N'At this point we had been at the site
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.84,0:52:32.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,似乎变得漫无止境了\N'for what seemed like an eternity
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.79,0:52:34.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而我们十分渴望回家\N'and we were desperate to get home
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.53,0:52:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,于是我们夜以继日地干活\N'so we were working\Nround the clock.'
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.66,0:52:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接住了？很沉的哦\NGot it? Yeah. That's a heavy...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.00,0:52:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,密度很高\NThat's a bit denser, that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.06,0:52:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我讨厌竹子\NI hate bamboo.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.62,0:52:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讨厌竹子\NI hate bamboo.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.12,0:52:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很讨厌\NSo much.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.83,0:52:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道么\NYou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.42,0:53:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,穿越缅甸后\Nafter that drive through Burma,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.44,0:53:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我心中获得的是对长途卡车司机的无限尊重\NI was left with an enormous amount of respect for long-distance lorry drivers.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.64,0:53:11.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是 此时此刻\NBut... Here, now,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.54,0:53:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我更敬重那些战俘们\NI have even more respect for those prisoners of war...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.04,0:53:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 没错\NOh, yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.69,0:53:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,严肃点 不开玩笑的说\NI mean, let's be honest, shall we,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.11,0:53:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们今晚要在这吃饭 -是的\Nwe are eating here at night. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.21,0:53:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们没得痢疾 没有霍乱\NWe haven't got dysentery and we haven't got cholera. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.77,0:53:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-也没每天被拳打脚踢 -是这样的\NAnd we're not been beaten, daily. No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.21,0:53:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就已经很难的 重活 累活\NI mean this is difficult, hard, hot work...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.76,0:53:35.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但都完全不算什么\NBut nothing... No. ..at all...You know
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.70,0:53:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你知不知道那个金属箱子 -嗯\Nthat metal box. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.93,0:53:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有个叫Drauer船长的人\NThere was a guy called Captain Drauer
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.96,0:53:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为弄坏了营长的桌子\Nwho broke the camp commandant's table.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.32,0:53:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被宣判在地下生活\NHe was sentenced to life underground and they buried him
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.16,0:53:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们把他关在一个金属箱子里暴露在阳光下\Nin one of those metal boxes with a metal roof exposed to the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.47,0:53:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他被关了76天 -天啊\Nand he was in there for 76 days. Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.00,0:54:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,关进去的时候 他的手折了\NHe had a broken arm when they put him in and when they got him out
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.66,0:54:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被放出来时 其中一只脚几乎被老鼠吃光\Nthe rats had eaten most of one of his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.85,0:54:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真的无法想象\NIt just beggars belief.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.41,0:54:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第十五天太阳升起的时候\N'As the sun rose on the 15th day,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.27,0:54:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,经历我们史上最艰难的任务\N'after the hardest work any of us had ever done,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.54,0:54:33.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大桥落成了\N'the bridge was finished.'
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.27,0:54:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真是值得庆祝的一刻\NThat is a proud moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.00,0:54:48.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是\NBut...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.90,0:54:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,桥有一点歪\NThere's a slope on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.80,0:54:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说的对 那一边肯定要高一点\NYou're right. It's definitely higher on that side.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.73,0:55:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们决定不在意这些细节\N'We decided to ignore the slope
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.00,0:55:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直接开始进行通车仪式\N'and move straight to the opening ceremony.'
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.00,0:55:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,三 二 一\NIn three, two, one...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.00,0:55:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我宣布 大桥通车啦\NI declare... ..the bridge open.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.58,0:55:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,伟大的时刻\NWhat a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.92,0:55:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,船长 你应该第一个过\NAnd James May, you shall cross it first.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.00,0:55:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么是我\NWhy am I crossing it first?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.40,0:55:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我说过了 “你应该第一个”\NBecause I just said, "James May, you shall cross it first".
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.24,0:55:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他的确说了 -我说了 -是的 毋庸置疑\NHe did, he said that. I did, didn't I? You did, you said that. Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.00,0:55:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,行吧\NRight...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.27,0:55:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幸运象 幸运猫头鹰\NLucky elephant, lucky owl,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.68,0:55:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,佛祖 出发\NBuddha, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.00,0:55:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我行驶在横跨湄 攻 河的桥上\NI on the bridge over the River Kok.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.47,0:56:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这绝对是我做过的最自虐的事了\NThis is genuinely the most nerve wracking thing I've ever done.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.45,0:56:12.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,詹姆斯 你很危险 他知道吗\NJames, you are perilously... Does he realise?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.28,0:56:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他太靠右了\NHe's a long way over to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.00,0:56:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冷静就好\NJust keep calm,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.00,0:56:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冷静\Nkeep calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.00,0:56:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天哪 桥叽叽嘎嘎地叫\NOh, my God! It's squirreling.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.00,0:56:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢 桥面裂了\NOh! They're rending.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.21,0:56:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已经走过半了\NI'm more than halfway across.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.36,0:56:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在只需开下去就好\NAll I've got to do is get down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.60,0:56:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开下去就完事了\NI just got to get down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.75,0:56:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快了\NI've almost done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.58,0:56:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拜托了\NPlease...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.00,0:56:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自己造桥自己过!\NI'm over the River Kok on our own bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.80,0:57:01.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来吧\NCome on!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.98,0:57:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你下一个吧\NCan you go next?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.00,0:57:07.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 我是下一个\NYes, I will go next. Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.81,0:57:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为你的车比我的重很多\NYes, because your lorry is a lot heavier than my lorry
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.12,0:57:11.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会损坏桥的\Nand will weaken it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.30,0:57:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,万万没想到\NI didn't think of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.84,0:57:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的宗旨是 速度和动力\NI have a policy here, speed and power.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.23,0:57:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为在我心里\NBecause, in my mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.44,0:57:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,速度可以让你变轻\Nspeed makes you lighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.16,0:57:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看不见桥面\NCan't see the bridge now.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.22,0:57:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来喽\NHere we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.52,0:57:39.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在"桂"河大桥上第一次换挡\NChange gear the first ever gear change on the bridge over the River Kok
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.43,0:57:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一次成功的换挡\Nand I bolst it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.57,0:57:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太靠中间了\NGetting too close to the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.25,0:57:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听着快散架了\NOh, the splintering noises.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.98,0:57:56.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在帮哈蒙德拆桥\NI'm weakening it for Hammond!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.00,0:58:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,加油 动感大卡!\NYes! Come on sports lorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.00,0:58:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好样的\NYes!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.27,0:58:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的动感大卡的门被搞坏了\NLook that the sports lorry has broken its door
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.00,0:58:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但它成功过桥 并为这一刻欢呼雀跃\Nbut it is across and is bouncing to celebrate the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.60,0:58:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太棒了\NYes!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.74,0:58:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在 该轮到最重的车了\N'Now it was the turn of the heaviest lorry of the lot.'
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.85,0:58:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的神啊\NOh, dear God.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.37,0:58:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我们自己造的桥\NThis is a bridge that we built.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.00,0:58:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实我真的很想让他掉下去\NI mean, obviously, I want him to fall into the Kok.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.00,0:58:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\NYes...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.00,0:58:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但如果掉下去 我们就回不了家了\NBut, if he does, we can't go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.00,0:58:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-挑战目标是三辆卡车都要成功 -没错\NThe challenge said all three lorries doing it. I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.59,0:58:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这辆卡车重达7.5吨\NThis struck is supposed to weigh 7.5 tonnes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.57,0:58:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道超载的那部分\NI don't know if that takes into consideration
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.65,0:58:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在不在桥的承受范围内\Nall the extra bits on top!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.37,0:58:56.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 天哪\NOh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.00,0:59:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢 我可以听到它在被挤压\NOh, I can hear it crushing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.88,0:59:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能感觉到它的移动\NI can feel it moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.95,0:59:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 不 怎么了\NOh, no, what's happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.96,0:59:12.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 不\NOh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.51,0:59:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我做了什么\NWhat have I done?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.70,0:59:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,桥快撑不住了\NIt's going at this end, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.63,0:59:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,结构垮塌了\NIt's losing structure!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.34,0:59:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,桥在分解\NIt's breaking apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.46,0:59:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,千万不要莽撞\NDon't rush to the end, Rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.00,0:59:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,继续像这样走\NJust go in your own...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.56,0:59:37.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,轻轻地走\NJust tiptoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.28,0:59:40.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正如轻轻地来\NJust tread lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.00,0:59:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不带走一根竹竿\NJust tiptoe your way across.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.48,0:59:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对 就这样\NThat's it. That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.63,0:59:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要想太多 往这边 往这边\NLight thoughts. This way, this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.78,0:59:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,向这边打方向\NThis way a bit. This way a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.56,0:59:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,向我们这打方向\NThis way a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.38,1:00:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这边啊 你要掉下去了\NThis way, this way, you're going to fall off.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.36,1:00:02.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要掉了\NYou're going to fall in!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.62,1:00:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈蒙德 理查德·哈蒙德\NHammond Richard Hammond!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.93,1:00:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,过去 我巴不得你挂掉\NI've never been glad to see you alive before
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.80,1:00:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但现在我不这么想了\Nbut I am now.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.86,1:00:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,差一点就掉下去了\NYou were so close.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.85,1:00:24.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们做到了\NWe did it. We did it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.66,1:00:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喔 对不起\NOw! Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.29,1:00:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,朋友\NMate...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.32,1:00:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道你最后几乎就要掉沟里了吗\NDo you know how close you were to falling into the middle at the end?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.00,1:00:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,半个轮胎\NHalf a tyre.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.08,1:00:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,半个轮胎挂在外面\NHalf a tyre over the edge.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.00,1:00:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是结果是\NThe fact is, though...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.71,1:00:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们三个都完成任务了\NAll three of us have done it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.00,1:00:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开着卡车过河\NWith our trucks, over the river.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.49,1:00:46.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,站在这里\NHere we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.67,1:00:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1920公里 造一座桥\N1,200 miles, built a bridge... Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.94,1:00:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开三辆卡车穿过来\N..drove all three lorries across it. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.00,1:00:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且成功了\NIt worked.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.45,1:00:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和电影"桂河大桥"不同\NUnlike the real film, Bridge On The River Kwai...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.00,1:01:00.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有爆炸性新闻\N..there is no bombshell.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.00,1:01:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有\NNo. No.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.25,1:01:04.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但也结束了\NBut there is an ending.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.65,1:01:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,感谢收看\NThanks very much for watching.\NThanks for watching.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.00,1:01:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多棒的旅程\NWhat a journey!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.00,1:01:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天啊 你真的就差一点\NYou were. You were close.
